  <h2>About IndieReel</h2>
<hr />

<p>IndieReel is a community where filmmakers of all backgrounds and experience levels can come together and do what they love: creating awesome films. Whether it's for kicks and giggles or serious business, this is where it's at. Search for other passionate indie individuals, look at projects that you would like to work on, and contribute to great productions. </p>

<hr />
  <h2>Why does it exist?</h2>
<hr />


<div class="row-fluid">
  <div class="span12">
    <p>In the foggy northern lands of California, there lies a most fantastical land of golden bears, fallen trees, and computer scientists – the perfect environment for fostering great software development. In Spring 2012, four figures emerged from the mist…</p><br>
    
    <div id="centered">
      <img src="../assets/csStaff.jpg" height="313" width="313">
    </div><br>
    
    <p>By some twist of fate, five lost children were drawn towards their light, and thus began our semester in CS169. We learned the secrets of SaaS, tamed Ruby into working code, and peeked at the wonders of pair programming. After our professors and TA's had educated us saplings with their words of wisdom, we were thrown out to the wild, straight into the arms of…</p>
    
    <div id="centered">
      <img src="../assets/john2.jpg" height="313" width="313">
    </div><br>
    
    <p>...our awesome customer, John. Ok. So maybe he didn’t exactly take us in like ducklings. But he was pretty badass, so we flocked to him anyways. You know, groupies. When John came up to us with a vision, we couldn't let him down. Thus, we embarked on the quest to make it a reality. We hemmed and hawed and hacked and danced and ate too many Fruit-by-the-foots and er…ahem..tested….</p>
    
    <div id="centered">
      <img src="../assets/comic.jpg" height="500" width="500">
    </div>
    
    <p>And after much random dancings, IndieReel was born. As you can see, it’s been quite a successful semester :]</p>
  </div>
</div>

